<font color="#FF0000">GOD BLESS AMERICA, ALWAYS!</font><br>
<tt>Fri Jan  2  3:13:05 US/Eastern 1998
</tt><p>
I don't choose to enter conversations with thieves, liars, dope heads, drunks, homosexuals, traitors, draft dodgers, whores, con men, atheists, idiots and cowards.<br>
I believe in a good work ethic, clean language, physical fitness, male and female roles, parenting, civic involvement, conservation of natural resources, and contractual committment.<br>
I know who I am and am not out seeking to find myself or make a mark on the world.  I love acceptance but will not prostitute myself or my values to get it or to fit in. I don't respect people who climb on the soap box and give half baked justifications for their business failures, divorces, criminal records, addictions, obesity or any other tangible evidence of failure to commit or abide by standards.  Nor do I appreciate arm chair quarterbacks who criticize freely but won't compete.<br>
Secondary to two years of intensive combat and thirty two years of indirect verbal abuse, I have adjusted to and developed an attitude of resentment toward anti-war protestors and other counterfiet slackards.  I feel reasonably sure that I despise war more than any anti-war protestor on Earth.  There is no need on my part to listen to why craven cowards fear war.<br>
Life is precious to me, my own included, but I would rather die a violent death than to live as a draft dodger hiding behind the skirts of stale logic, tailored history and the short comings of other men.<br><br>
Captain Edward Ramon- U.S. Army Fifth Special Forces &quot;Omega&quot;-U.S. Naval Special Operations Seal Team Two &quot;Seawolf&quot;- RVN'66'67'69
